data.text:
Saturday, Sept 16th is the 9th annual Johnny Carson Birthplace Car Show in Corning, Iowa.

It’s held at Davies Avenue and the block surrounding the park next to the courthouse and the Corning Opera House.

The Southwest Cruisers of Iowa, Car Club hosts the car show. Admission is free to attend and check out the variety of cars. To register and display your vehicle is just $20. Classes include stock and modified cars, stock and modified trucks, and motorcycles.

While you’re in Corning, I would highly recommend calling ahead for reservations at Primrose Restaurant or stopping in at Fire & Salt Co to check out the meat market, seasons, oils, or cigars! Or check out our larger listing of Things to do in Corning, Iowa

Location: Davis Avenue in Corning, Iowa
